Class DLLNode<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • DLLNode<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDLLNode<T>

    public class DLLNode<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDLLNode<T>
    Class to handle a node for a doubly-linked list. This code implements a standard node in a doubly-linked list. Instance variables are next, prev, nodeData, and all but the last are standard and no methods exist here except the accessors and mutators for the instance variables and the standard toString that returns a formatted version of the data payload. Note that this hard-codes the data payload as an item of Basket type, and this ought to be reworked to use generics. Copyright (C) 2012 by Duncan A. Buell. All rights reserved. Used and modified with permission by chongwen guo student.

    1.00 2012-01-01
    Author:
